The '''United States Senate election of 1884''' was an election which had the [[Republican Party (United States)| Republican Party]] gain four seats in the [[United States Senate]], and which coincided with the [[United States presidential election, 1884|presidential election of 1884]].

As this election was prior to ratification of the [[Seventeenth Amendment to the United States Constitution|seventeenth amendment]], Senators were chosen by [[State legislature (United States)|State legislatures]].

== Results ==
[[49th United States Congress|49th Congress]] (1885â1887) 

* Majority Party: Republican (42)
* Minority Party: Democratic (34)
* Other Parties: (0)
* '''Total Seats: 76'''

